# Action Items Console — no server-side configuration required.
#
# All scope is passed by the HOST on the iframe URL and read client-side:
#   /?env=<uat|stag|prod>&enterpriseId=<id>&teamId=<id>&token=<bearer>
#     optional: &department=sales|service&userId=<id>&userEmail=<email>
#
# The browser calls the Spyne backend DIRECTLY (base URL derived from `env`):
#   uat  → https://uat-api.spyne.xyz
#   stag → https://beta-api.spyne.xyz
#   prod → https://api.spyne.ai
#
# There are NO server-side secrets. The bearer token comes from the URL, never from env.
# The only server route (/api/call-recording) is a token-free same-origin streamer that pipes
# S3 audio bytes to the waveform player (S3 sends no CORS header); it needs no configuration.

# ── PostHog product analytics (optional) ──────────────────────────────────────
# Analytics is OFF until a project key is set — the app runs identically without it.
# Get the key from PostHog → Project Settings → Project API Key.
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_KEY     project API key (public, safe to expose)   e.g. phc_xxx
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_HOST    "/ingest" to use the same-origin reverse proxy (recommended)
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_REGION  "us" (default) or "eu" — must match your PostHog project region
# NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_KEY=
# NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_HOST=/ingest
# NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_REGION=us
